<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-08-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="302" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1501.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-08-05"><hi rend="italic">
                                        August</hi> 5, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 20th ultimo, No. 1017, transmitting, through the agency
                            of Mr. Morse, our consul at London, the depositions of certain parties,
                            which fully indicate the part taken by the steamer City of Richmond in
                            supplying the Stonewall with armament and crew.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>